Package: dsImaging
Type: Package
Title: DataSHIELD Medical Imaging Datasets
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    c(person("David", "Sarrat González", , "david.sarrat@isglobal.org", role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Xavier", "Escribà-Montagut", , "xavier.escriba@isglobal.org", role = c("aut")),
      person("Juan R", "González", , "juanr.gonzalez@isglobal.org", role = c("aut")))
Description: Server-side DataSHIELD package for medical imaging datasets.
    Provides manifest-based dataset descriptors, a SQLite asset catalog for
    immutable derived assets (masks, radiomics tables, embeddings, etc.),
    resource resolvers for the resourcer ecosystem (imaging+dataset:// URLs),
    and DataSHIELD methods for secure imaging dataset management. Assets are
    content-addressed via derivation hash for deduplication, support lineage
    tracking, and can be referenced via human-friendly aliases.
